The paper discusses a new framework for data-dependent DNN regularization, which is a topic commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper also focuses on improving the discriminative power of features, which is a common goal in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of numerical experiments, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
